thread.title: Austin volleyball still perfect in district, ranked No. 2 in state
thread.title_full: Austin volleyball still perfect in district, ranked No. 2 in state

author: Jack Marrion jmarrion@hcnonline.com
title: Austin volleyball still perfect in district, ranked No. 2 in state
text:
Advertisement Posted: Thursday, October 1, 2015 10:45 am | Updated: 10:52 am, Thu Oct 1, 2015. Austin volleyball still perfect in district, ranked No. 2 in state By Jack Marrion jmarrion@hcnonline.com Houston Community Newspapers 
The Austin volleyball team remains unstoppable in District 23-6A. After a sweep of Hightower on Sept. 29, the Lady Bulldogs’ district streak of consecutive sets won reached 75, covering 25 matches. 
Austin (33-2) has also fared well against non-district opponents, earning the attention of the Texas Girls Coaches Association. The Lady Bulldogs are now ranked No. 2 in the state, behind only Southlake Carroll (33-3). 
They are 9-0 in district play with seven matches remaining. Against Hightower, Madison Rhoder led the offense with eight kills, followed by Erin Mulcahey and Paige Swinney, both of whom served two aces. Erin Anthony (16 assists) and Maddie Nicholson (12 assists) shared the setting duties in a 25-10, 25-13, 25-14 victory 
The Lady Bulldogs hold a one-match lead in the 23-6A standings, as Dulles improved to 8-1 with a 25-12, 25-11, 25-14 sweep of Elsik. Chandler Marshall turned in 13 kills. 
Clements defeated Kempner in three, 25-11, 25-17, 25-17 to improve to 7-2 in district. Kempner was led by Dani Edmunds’ eight kills, with Sarah Argo (six kills, nine digs), Vianca Jiminez (nine digs) and Brandy Howen (17 assists) among the statistical leaders. 
Travis is 6-3 after a 25-11, 25-4, 25-10 rout of Alief Taylor. Destiny Jones recorded seven kills in 11 attempts, adding two blocks and three aces. Lauren Clarke had seven kills. Raven Robertson amassed three aces and 17 digs. Kendall Wolfe and Riley Marsh combined for 21 assists. 
In District 23-5A, Marshall was the only Fort Bend ISD winner with a 25-7, 24-26, 25-7, 25-11 victory against Willowridge. The Lady Buffalos rose to sixth place, one match from a playoff spot. 
Bush fell to 4-2 in district with a five-set loss to Ball, 21-25, 25-19, 20-25, 25-23, 15-8. Texas City handed Ridge Point its first loss 25-23, 25-27, 25-19, 25-20, dropping the Lady Panthers to 5-1 behind unbeaten Santa Fe, which defeated Elkins 25-13, 25-12, 25-13. 
DISTRICT 23-6A
